CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 14, 1962, pg. 2 reads: "Seeking Job Opportunities - Among those seeking equal employment opportunities are the above four of the 50 persons who registered at Wesley Center AME Zion Church. Left to right: James E. Wilbanks, Mrs. Martha B. Johnson, Mrs. Ida Joyce Sharp, Leo Breedlove (chairman, HRC), Charles Franklin.  Standing is Rev. Charles Foggie, pastor."
TitMainTitle: Human Relations Committee members, from left: James E. Wilbanks, Martha B. Johnson, Ida Joyce Sharp, chairman Leo Breedlove, Rev. Charles Foggie, and Charles Franklin, gathered behind table in Wesley Center AME Zion Church
